        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Collection consists of materials dating from 1852 to 1912 and includes loose ledger
                sheets for the household expenditures of Dr. John B. Slusser, an advertisement from
                the Pressed Steel Car Company, a reciept from the Virginia Tech dining hall, a
                United States patent application for a nut-lock invented by Murray C. and William J.
                Slusser, and pages from a personal account book. </p>
        </scopecontent>
